      <title>Slow down the Leveling race.........</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=162325#M162325</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I have posted my views on leveling before, and am in favor of doing something to slow down the race to level 70 that every new player seems to get into. I have even seen posts from Dev's where they refer to getting to level 70 so you can &amp;quot;start the game&amp;quot;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Seems to me, that Sony would not want that, as it allows someone to get to the end game so fast that after 9 months, you have no reason to stick to the game.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;One of the big reasons people run for level 70, is that AA's come so much faster at level 70. 2 AA's an hour is doable. So, why stop at 51 to get AA's? Why stop at 60? or 65?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I think that AA experience should be leveled for all levels................&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;In other words, make AA's come just as fast for a level 51 as they do for Level 70.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;This will be an incentive to players to stop at level 51, and 55, and 60 etc, to get some AA's to make them more powerful, and to experience some of the abilitys that were TUNED for those levels. Those AA's were DESIGNED for characters of that level to use, but the slow AA progression encourages players to skip AA's till they get much higher in level. This change will encourage players to experience the content that is available to those levels and get something tangeable in return.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Kunnar on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;01-13-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;03:58 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
