      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;There is only a race if you chose to run.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The only people that make the "race" to 70 are the people that are running.&amp;nbsp; It is not designed into the game, except yeah, there are some pretty long stretches of pretty boring levels.&amp;nbsp; You don't need to.&amp;nbsp; You don't have to.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Games are supposed to be about having fun.&amp;nbsp; I have fun or I don't log in, and I haven't hit 70 yet with any of my characters in 5+ years of playing and 3 accounts.&amp;nbsp; I don't care for raiding so I don't do it.&amp;nbsp; I don't care for grouping with people who are after the most efficient killing experience, so I don't.&amp;nbsp; I could be getting the best experience in all the game, but if I am in a group where no one talks, I am going to leave.&amp;nbsp; I refuse to join any group that inspects me or asks me numbers (like mana or ac or whatever)&amp;nbsp;before joining.&amp;nbsp; I like being in groups of people who are yes, good at their class, but who are also good at having fun.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;No one makes me race to 70.&amp;nbsp; No one makes me stay at 62 or whatever level I may be that day.&amp;nbsp; I have goals that require leveling, I have goals that don't.&amp;nbsp; I didn't succumb to peer pressure when I was 15, I don't succumb to it when I am 45.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;rat a tat tat (the sound of a different drum)&lt;/P&gt;</description>
