      <title>Re: Slow down the Leveling race.........</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=175804#M175804</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Lower level content is what attracts new players. That is the first thing they see upon entering the game. If there were better zones to attract old players there with their alts as well as new players with their mains, the zones would be populated and provide grouping possiblities for new players. That would, in turn, encourage those new players to recommend the game to their friends, thus bringing even more players in. It would give new players a real opportunity to learn their class and have fun leveling progressively instead of hurrying through MM leveling to 'reach the game'. Why in the world should the game begin at 65 or 70?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;That mindset is what has caused the decline of new players to the game and the ridiculous idea that one should need to level up quickly to have any fun. Why can't lower levels be fun too? Why can't there be gear upgrades and spell drops from mobs in lower level zones? Why shouldn't the game be fun regardless of your level? Us veteran players will still be here as long as high level content is continually added but new players will continue to disappear if they are not given some attention.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;There should be zones like WoS for low levels. For goodness sakes, even the tutorial has a named mob that looks like Velitorkin. There should be gear quests and spell drops ( I don't care if you can buy the spells from vendors, new players don't have much money). I can say with relative surety that if there was at least one static zone for progressive levels with nameds to kill, spell drops, gear drops, quest drops and decent experience those zones would be populated all the time and make finding a group easier for new players. Bringing in new players and providing them places to advance their characters, learn their class, develop their skills and have fun doing it is going to be vital for the future of EQ. Since the current static zones do not have anything to attract new players to them or even older players with their alts, they will remain wastelands.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
