 back to game play. Those who are subjugating themselves to the litany of MMs to the point that the level 70 pool has been diluted with what I refer to as &amp;quot;fake&amp;quot; 70's.  Those who don't know how the play their class.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And in case you're wondering, I started playing this game when LDoN came out and have loved it since level 1. I gave away the rarest of things in Ultima out to total strangers after playing this game for a week.  If I find something that I like better than EQ, I'll shut off my accounts and give away my stuff that I can and stop playing! I'm not going to come on these boards and whine and complain that it's SoE's fault or it's soandso's fault that I don't like the game. If I don't like it, it means I don't like it. Do you like Anchovies? I don't, so I don't eat them. But I don't call up the maker of the Anchovies and whine and complain.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Yes the game is flooded with high level characters, but you know what? That's not going to change! Leveling now is faster than when I started, and so be it. It took me a year and a half to get to 70 on my cleric but I took a few pit stops... I have done long drawn out quests and enjoyed the game as I leveled! (Weird, eh?)  Mind you my ranger hit 70 in 9 months, but I took the necessary pit-stops to get AAs crucial to my class. Ever have a 70 cleric hit you with 150 min Conviction? Does it upset you? It does me, but I don't say anything because I'm still happy that I have the buff.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;So 3 cheers to the Devs, Designers, Testers, Coders, Conceptual Artists, and GMs. Keep delivering us a great product and keep up the good work! And to those of you who want to complain about them, think about what they go through every day when they go to work. If you want a good example of what they go through, make a city in SimCity and make everyone in the entire city happy. It's not possible!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And if you think the game is great the way it is, Let them know! They will be more than happy to hear that! Unfortunately, the way society is today, people only ask to see the manager if they're angry. People only post comments that are negative. Happy people are quiet because they are using the product. This is true in any industry.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
